  "bib_entries": {
    "104200981": {
      "title": "Studies on solubility enhancement and in vitro dissolution profile of poorly water soluble drug atenolol using solid dispersion technique",
      "abstract": "The objective of present study was to improve the aqueous solubility and dissolution rate of poorly water-soluble drug Atenolol by solid dispersion technique. The method of preparation used was Solvent Evaporation Method, using a hydrophilic carrier polyethylene glycol 6000 (PEG 6000). The study was further aimed to characterize prepared solid dispersions in the solid state by Fourier Transform Infrared Spectroscopy (FTIR), and Powder X-Ray Diffraction (PXRD) patterns. Dissolution Studies were carried out to find out percentage released content of drug as a function of time. UV Spectroscopy method was used to find out drug contents in all the samples."
